<Project>

  <!--
    FullHouse.props - shared "raise the co-op lobby cap" engine (namespace DooDesch.Lobbies) for
    Schedule I MelonLoader mods. Lives in the public Stash repo (github.com/DooDesch-Mods/ScheduleOne-Stash).

    A mod opts in with EXACTLY ONE line - IMPORTANT: place it AFTER the mod's <Compile Remove="Stash/**/*.cs" />
    ItemGroup (CI checks the Stash out as a subfolder, so without the Remove the SDK glob would double-include
    the file this props adds):
        <Import Project="$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)../Stash/build/FullHouse.props"
                Condition="Exists('$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)../Stash/build/FullHouse.props')" />

    Usage in the host mod: call DooDesch.Lobbies.FullHouse.Install() once, early (e.g. OnInitializeMelon).
    That raises the cap natively - no external BiggerLobbies dependency. Coexists with other cap mods
    (highest cap wins) and a runtime single-flight guard prevents double-patching if the standalone
    FullHouse.dll is also loaded.

    The engine is INTERNAL and compiled into each consumer assembly separately, so there is NO CS0436 risk
    even when one consumer references another consumer's DLL. It needs MelonLoader + 0Harmony + the game's
    Networking/UI.Multiplayer types + Steamworks + UnityEngine.UI - all of which a multiplayer host mod
    already references. The FULLHOUSE_STANDALONE symbol (defined only by the standalone FullHouse.csproj)
    is left OFF here, so the MelonMod entry point compiles out and the host drives the engine directly.
  -->

  <ItemGroup>
    <Compile Include="$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)..\fullhouse\FullHouse.cs" Link="FullHouse\FullHouse.cs" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
